rComments: Rob is awesome. Very knowledgeable and personally supportive - he was the only prof who supported me when I wanted to transfer, rather than trying to convince me to stay at the school. Also very involved in reforming the curriculum, which shows his dedication to the job. Definitely recommend.

A great, HILARIOUS man with good heart who actually gives a crap about his students. But if I learned anything during his tangential lectures it was accidental. His emails and talks with you are much more helpful. Great guy.

Carson genuinely cares and he's really easy to approach when it comes to needing help or extensions. As for the lectures, I didn't find any of them relevant. He usually rambled on about how he would stage the play rather than analyze it and often went off topic. Great guy, he really is, but the class itself was "meh".
This guy made me WANT to come to class. A good prof with HILARIOUS delivery. If he taught the phone book I would take it.
Rob...u are an awesome prof!!Keep up the good work and good luck with your band!

Really awesome teacher! Lot's of pop culture references which help you get a grasp on the concepts in class. He's in a a band (Rock Plaza Central) and I guess they are getting alot of buzz on pitchfork and stuff. I hope he doesn't leave UofT to become a rock star!!!!! He is so good at his job, and it would be a really big loss.

Professor Carson was enthusiastic, funny (often accidentally), knowledgeable, and very approachable. He wasn't awkward about telling students where they were going wrong, and was great about telling them where they were right. He was one of my best professors, and a great person outside of the classroom. You'd be a fool to miss out on this man.
